Around the Wordle in 365 days

An analysis of one year of Wordle

Surbhi Bhatia

2023-01-11

Tracy would dream weird words every night. [Adults plays, make guess, phone, world] [Share] Social media posts would ensue later, daily. There is no other way to describe the Wordle-wide global phenomenon, than to respect the games one rule: Five-letter words only. It is no coincidence that the Wordle editor, Tracy Benett, has a five-lettered name too. Its the main qualification. And we need someone to BLAME for our X/6 downfalls, many times a week.

[Made by Josh Wardle, wordle was born on June 19, 2021, NYT acquired it - Jan 31, 2022. Share button added on December 16, 2021. [https://twitter.com/powerlanguish/status/1471493886031773707?s=20&t=WJv0F2f_KMUHt0vGWTIyjA] 2022 was the year of Wordle. It was the most googled search globally. People were sharing green and black boxes of scores all over.]

NYT time was also peak of sharing results on Twitter. In the one year period between Jan 7, when the Wordle BOT started collecting these tweets, 32 million tweets were recorded. The interest seems to be waning. The number of people posting their scores by end of 2022 were ten times fewer than in Feb-March 2022.
